* Long division is used when the divisor is not a binomial or when the binomial does not have a leading coefficient of 1.
* Synthetic division only works when dividing by a linear binomial of the form [x - c] or [x + c].
* The Remainder Theorem: If a polynomial [f(x)] is divided by [x - c], the remainder is [f(c)].
* The Factor Theorem: [x - c] is a factor of [f(x)] if and only if [f(c) = 0].
* If the remainder is [0], the divisor is a factor of the dividend.
